		Player: "Maisa wants to speak with you."
		Osman: "You must be mistaken. She's in Menaphos and that city is locked tight to everyone, thanks in no small part to me."
		Player: "What? What have you been up to there?"
		Osman: "Nothing out of the ordinary. I've had my people instigate a bit of civil unrest. Officially our cities may be at peace, but I have some old scores to settle first."
		Player: "Look, one of your people, Kaleef, is dead and the contact he was meant to meet in the tunnels under the river demands to see you."
		Player: "She wants to get out of Menaphos."
		Osman: "Ah, Maisa, a great talent but far too highly strung. I should have known. I'll send one of my people to sort her out shortly."
		Player: "She wanted you to come in person."
		Osman: "I can't do that; that would be tantamount to sticking one's head in a crocodile's mouth."
		Osman: "I would be lynched on sight if I were to be found."
		Player: "What's the deal between yourself and the Menaphites?"
		Osman: "Our two kingdoms were at war with one another for centuries. They tried to expand their kingdom northwards many times over the years, but we held them off."
		Player: "Wow, that's impressive, seeing as you don't have much of an army."
